body:
The following code:

```rust
fn foo(val: &mut bool) {
    match (val, true) {
        _ => { val; }
    }
}
```

results in the following error:

```
error[E0382]: use of moved value: `val`
 --> src/lib.rs:3:16
  |
1 | fn foo(val: &mut bool) {
  |        --- move occurs because `val` has type `&mut bool`, which does not implement the `Copy` trait
2 |     match (val, true) {
  |            --- value moved here
3 |         _ => { val; }
  |                ^^^ value used here after move

error: aborting due to previous error
```

We should suggest `match (&mut *val, true)`, which will make this compile.

Note that the following code *does* compile:

```rust
fn foo(val: &mut bool) {
    match val {
        _ => { val; }
    }
}
```

It looks like we automatically insert a reborrow under some circumstances.
